# AU Micro-SaaS Portfolio — Smart Token + Multi-Model Rules
# Cursor Pro A$20/mo | 50-55 bets | cheap-first, escalate only when stuck

## Default Model (start here every time)
- Auto mode OR Haiku 4.5 — pick one, don't jump to premium
- Cmd+K + Haiku 4.5 for 80%+ of edits (no chat context cost)
- Tab autocomplete for routine typing (essentially free)

## Smart Multi-Model Escalation Ladder
Use the cheapest step that works. Never skip steps.

1. Haiku 4.5 / Luna / Flash — plan, schema, code, fixes, prompts (90%+ of work)
2. Opus 4.5/4.6/4.7 (FREE) — complex schema or security review when Haiku fails
3. Sonnet 5 — complex logic after free Opus fails (max 5-10 calls/month)
4. Frontier (Fable 5 / Opus 4.8 / GPT-5.6 Sol) — LAST RESORT, 1-2 calls/month TOTAL across all bets, only for bets with paying customers

## Task → Model Map
| Task | Model | Why |
|------|-------|-----|
| Inline edit, rename, docstring | Cmd+K + Haiku 4.5 | Cheapest, no chat context |
| Boilerplate, config, types | Luna or Flash | Trivial generation |
| Day-1 scaffold (multi-file) | Composer (Auto) | One session per MVP |
| Schema, file plan, ISC | Haiku 4.5 | Cheap enough for planning |
| Complex schema / security | Opus 4.5 free | Free escalation |
| Stuck on hard logic | Sonnet 5 | Paid escalation |
| Debug specific bug | BugBot | 22% cheaper than chat |
| Unsure which model | Auto mode | Cursor picks cheapest adequate |
| Big codebase read (100K+) | Gemini 3.1 Pro | Long context only when needed |

## Token Rules (non-negotiable)
- One chat per feature — don't open new chats per file
- @ mention 2-3 files max — never dump whole codebase
- .cursorrules = free instructions (this file) — don't repeat in prompts
- Snippets for Stripe, Supabase, auth — saves 200+ tokens per use
- Composer once per MVP for scaffold — then Cmd+K only
- Cut failing bets at 7 days — don't pour tokens into dead experiments
- Frontier models ONLY on bets with revenue signal

## Build Loop (token-budgeted)
1. PLAN — Haiku 4.5, 1 call, 2-5K tokens
2. BUILD — Composer (Auto) scaffold + Haiku Cmd+K edits, 10-25K tokens
3. TEST — no AI
4. VERIFY — Haiku 4.5, 1-2K tokens; escalate only if stuck
5. FINALIZE — document, cut or continue

## Stack Defaults
- Next.js 14+ (App Router), Tailwind, shadcn/ui
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth) or FastAPI
- Stripe (AU), Vercel, Resend
- AU dates DD/MM/YYYY, currency AUD, timezone Australia/Sydney

## Portfolio Rules
- 50-55 bets, expect 1-2 winners (2.5% rule)
- 7-day cut rule for zero-traction bets
- Friday portfolio review
- Document outcomes in /reports/
